body:
An excise; a tax on movables;
a rent, custom, or service. Co. Litt. 213.
—Land gabel. See LAND.

In old English law.
Garniture; whatever is necessary for the fortification of a city or camp, or for the ornament of a thing. 8 Rymer, 328; Du Cange;
Cowell; Blount.

L. Fr. Wastel; wastel bread;
the finest sort of wheat. bread. Britt. c. 30;
Kelham.

In Saxon law. To convey;
to transfer boc land, (book-land or Jand held
by charter.) The grantor was said to gebocian the alienee. See 1 Reeve, Eng. Law, 10.

In Spanish law. A right of way
for narrow carts. White, New Recop. L 2,

ce. 6, § 1. _
